<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: So is a bow superior to a hand held melee weapon?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Stupid">Stupid</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:47 p.m. 7/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: So is a bow superior to a hand held melee weapon?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2060" TARGET=_self>So is a bow superior to a hand held melee weapon?</A> (TheBlack)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I dueled fighters with my Shaman at low levels 8-13 and I beat

<BR>&gt; them consistently
<P>Up to about level 15, a Shaman can stand toe to toe with a same level Warrior and have a good chance of emerging victorious. The Shaman can attack with a weapon, bash with his shield, cast direct damage and heal himself as needed. The warrior can attack with his weapon, maybe bash (depending on race), and kick. Who do you expect to win?
<P>This all changes at level 15, when the warrior turns into a slice-o-matic with dual wield+double attack, bash/slam, dodge, parry! thrust! spin! hoo! ha! Anything above the mid teens and the Shaman can't win unlkess he is VERY lucky or very sneaky (or both).
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
